ludes certain libraries like com.thoughtworks.proxy. I wonder if the agent records only library reflection. Maybe existing tests can compile with native generated configs without worry? But if the test triggers library reflection, it could cause config exclusions and fail. I'll consider using a JDK delegate instead to reduce configuration issues, ensuring I also assert the expected behavior. It seems native might support reflection on JDK, which is interesting!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_ZSAq7lUAIahaFLWrvysInV3z|fc_072c9b710878e5fd0169f10ae96e0481908db75c49f60bf36c\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.thoughtworks.proxytoys/proxytoys/1.0/main/extracted/com/thoughtworks/proxy/kit/ObjectReference.java\", \"limit\": 100}}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_KgffzhiEVdJQqfXy2nMBtBYw|fc_072c9b710878e5fd0169f10ae96e188190afbf2bdb48eb0615\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.thoughtworks.proxytoys/proxytoys/1.0/main/extracted/com/thoughtworks/proxy/kit/SimpleReference.java\", \"limit\": 120}}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_Zo65xFBC5Zf4VsBjoRjScDwA|fc_072c9b710878e5fd0169f10ae96e208190b6d9feffce706bcc\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.thoughtworks.proxytoys/proxytoys/1.0/main/extracted/com/thoughtworks/proxy/factory/StandardProxyFactory.java\", \"limit\": 220}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 496, \"output\": 941, \"cacheRead\": 15872, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 17309, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777404636338, \"responseId\": \"resp_072c9b710878e5fd0169f10adcab